def count_inversions(arr):
    inv_count = 0
    for i in range(len(arr)):
        for j in range(i + 1, len(arr)):
            if arr[i] > arr[j]:
                inv_count += 1
    return inv_count
```

This function iterates through the list and counts how many times an element at index `i` is greater than the element at a later index `j`. This approach has a time complexity of O(n^2) due to the nested loops, so it may not be efficient for very large lists. If performance on larger datasets is needed, an O(n log n) algorithm using merge sort can be implemented as well.

